The paper deals with termination of higher-order functions and uses System F-omega, which is a type system for polymorphic lambda calculus. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) and Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the encoding of inductive data types, which falls under the category of Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL). Additionally, the paper deals with rewrite rules, which is a topic in Theoretical Computer Science (cs.TL) and the termination of algorithms, which is a topic in Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
